President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key Administration posts. Caitlin Durkovich will be appointed as Assistant Secretary for Infrastructure Protection at the Department of Homeland Security. She currently serves as the Chief of Staff of the National Protection and Programs Directorate at the Department of Homeland Security. Ellen M. Peel will be appointed as the United States Commissioner for the International Commission for the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas. She is currently the President of The Billfish Foundation and has previously served as the Acting Regional Director for the Center for Marine Conservation. Russell F. Smith III will also be appointed as the United States Commissioner for the International Commission for the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas. He currently serves as the Deputy Assistant Secretary for International Fisheries at the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration.